Robin van Persie on Arsenal&rsquo;s passive approach to the game against Man Utd: &ldquo;Even though it&rsquo;s away, it doesn&rsquo;t matter, this is a big game. Just go at them &amp; try to win the ball high, play in their half, play positive. I would like to see a better game plan.&rdquo; [Optus Sports] #afc<br />
<br />
Van Persie: &ldquo;In the first 25 minutes of the game, you could see they were dropping back a lot, quite deep. If you choose as a coach &amp; players to do that, it&rsquo;s fine, but then you need to have runners. You need to have at least two runners once you get the ball which I didn&rsquo;t see.&rdquo;

